fg_segments: Privacy Policy At ExtraImage, we try to offer some of the best free services possible.
We understand that offering a free hosting service opens the doors to abuse.
We do not condone the uploading of copyright-infringing or otherwise illegal content to our servers, nor do we want to be hosting it.
If you believe your intellectual property rights are being violated, please do not hesitate to contact us.
We will have the content removed as soon as humanly possible.
DMCA Takedown Request Please include the following information in your removal request: •
An electronic or physical signature of the person authorized to act on behalf of the intellectual property owner.
• A description of the intellectual property being infringed upon .
• The URL on extraimage.net where the file is being hosted .
• Your contact information, including name, address, telephone, and email .
• A statement of good faith that the disputed use is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the low .

• Your statement, made under penalty of perjury, that the above information included in your notice is accurate and that you are either the copyright owner or authorized to act on the owner's behalf .
Please send your violation notice, including all of the above mentioned pieces of information to us by using the contact page and by choosing DMCA as subject.

At ExtraImage, we try to offer some of the best free services possible. We understand that offering a free hosting service opens the doors to abuse. We do not condone the uploading of copyright-infringing or otherwise illegal content to our servers, nor do we want to be hosting it. If you believe your intellectual property rights are being violated, please do not hesitate to contact us. We will have the content removed as soon as humanly possible. DMCA Takedown Request

 • An electronic or physical signature of the person authorized to act on behalf of the intellectual property owner.

 • Your contact information, including name, address, telephone, and email .
 • A statement of good faith that the disputed use is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the low .
 • Your statement, made under penalty of perjury, that the above information included in your notice is accurate and that you are either the copyright owner or authorized to act on the owner's behalf .
